headline: Deere Boosts Outlook, Sees Construction, Small Agriculture Demand Recovering
summary: Deere  raised its fiscal-year outlook and said demand in the construction and small agriculture markets was recovering.  The company posted first-quarter net income of $656 million, or $2.42 a share, down from $869 million, or $3.19 a share, the year before.  Net sales and revenue rose 13% to $9.61 billion, boosted by a 34% increase in net sales for its construction and forestry division and 24% net sales growth for its small agriculture and turf segment.
